Package civitas.celestis.math.vector

Interface Vector<N extends Number,V extends Vector<N,V>>

Type Parameters:
N - The type of number this vector is composed of
V - The vector itself (the result and parameter of various operations)
All Superinterfaces:
Collectable<N>, Groupable<N>, Listable<N>, Serializable, Transformable<N>
All Known Subinterfaces:
BigVector<N,V>, DecimalVector<V>, DoubleVector<V>, FloatVector<V>
All Known Implementing Classes:
ArrayVector, Decimal2, Decimal3, Decimal4, DecimalArrayVector, DecimalQuaternion, Float2, Float3, Float4, LinearColor, Quaternion, Vector2, Vector3, Vector4
public interface Vector<N extends Number,V extends Vector<N,V>> extends Transformable<N>, Groupable<N>, Listable<N>, Serializable
A mathematical vector. Vectors are a one-dimensional array of numbers.

Like Tuples, vectors are immutable, but are different in that they can hold primitive types in their raw unboxed form. Vectors can be converted into tuples by calling Groupable.group().

    • equals

      boolean equals(@Nullable Object obj)
      Checks for equality between this vector and the provided object obj. This will check if the other object is also a vector, and then compare the length and components.

      If the two vectors have the same length and every component has the same numerical value, this will return true.
